OVERVIEW: Add a target to a scheme's build action

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli add-scheme-target [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] <scheme-name> <target-name> [--action <action>]

ARGUMENTS:
  <scheme-name>           Name of the scheme to modify
  <target-name>           Name of the target to add

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  --action <action>       Comma-separated list of actions
                          (build,test,run,profile,archive,analyze). Default:
                          all actions
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

